article.description: Darrell Brown had 21 points as Bradley got past Loyola-Chicago 61-54 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Brown carries Bradley past Loyola-Chicago 61-54
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Darrell Brown had 21 points as Bradley got past Loyola-Chicago 61-54 on Wednesday night. Elijah Childs had 13 points and seven rebounds for Bradley (14-12, 6-7 Missouri Valley Conference). Luuk van Bree added 11 points and 10 rebounds. Marques Townes had 15 points and seven rebounds for the Ramblers (16-10, 9-4). Cameron Krutwig added 13 points and 11 rebounds. Bradley plays Illinois State on the road on Saturday. Loyola of Chicago plays Missouri State at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
